;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="968" y="70" width="287" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Time of perils:&lt;br&gt;space settlement exits it&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+11+14]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   930k lives-eq/$1k · 68% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 24%&lt;br&gt;(Toby Ord, Elon Musk)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + resilience_undermines_deterrence + time_of_perils_exit&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Time-of-perils optimism: hazard is high during the AI / nuclear transition but collapses once decorrelated, self-sufficient settlements exist — no single catastrophe reaches them all. The window closes, the expected future stretches far past the background-hazard baseline, and x-risk reduction during the window is what unlocks it (Ord, The Precipice; the multiplanetary-backup argument). Mutually exclusive with the view that early expansion re-arms the hazard. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence → 14 time_of_perils_exit" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWWtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6unbUdyW8nmwHSxpkpNn0gSXcwaAqXlmibG1nSklQct9P57XtISrac2Ig7%2BRIoEnnuuU%2FeS387CPmEZZF%2BnYT84Pjg6IhOT0%2FpRjIRk04okOzrEg%2BLmG6zpue3aZHIKLwXfEELf9QcdUbdUX%2Fk%2ByN8qiidpOS3qwbjNgbWmVLZPNUiiSmYAfKYPEqZTIKZYJFB9AdN8mnC5Igt2HI0y%2BYsVsWHJrFYzFmkRiqZ88WM6eJLhyaZziTPN4zmTGsuRwuhZ6NQqCDJYi3iabG8S3FSfj%2Fa2F2s6pPKJhMu7YIkyBQPVxR9klyJSPA44KMsDrmci5irUcghV5q3q6Vt0mLOR8lklAIL5PmD0NYaQxbMiK1NIhQx%2BrDUMzxPRMQJNl9%2FVkekjcosDFUN4uEoI5ISacEkr8OSbG4ICIX3esadkf%2BhYJ04sBgnFCTzNFHGGKsF2Gs0gHp6JpRFU5rFIYuSmNMckRA16MvK0cP7L4aq2c4fUh5obLxnUcYpmViEdUw0LNgrrjSNsyVZQ5